what are the types of verbs?
There are several types of verbs, including: 1. Action verbs - These describe an action or physical movement (e.g., run, jump). 2. Linking verbs - These connect two things in a relationship (e.g., is, was, seems). 3. State-of-being verbs - These express the state of being of something (e.g., exists, appears). 4. Helping verbs - These help another verb to form a complex tense or expression (e.g., have, can, will). 5. Emphatic verbs - These are used for emphasis and are often repeated in different forms (e.g., very, really, absolutely).
